## Proposed Changes

### Data Layer

#### [NEW] [data_loader.py](file:///c:/Users/RABUL/Desktop/mll/src/data_loader.py)
- Auto-downloads the Cleveland Heart Disease dataset via `ucimlrepo`
- Returns a raw pandas DataFrame with the `num` target column (0–4)

#### [NEW] [preprocessing.py](file:///c:/Users/RABUL/Desktop/mll/src/preprocessing.py)
- Handles missing values (a few `?` values in `ca` and `thal` columns)
- Encodes categorical features (e.g. `thal`, `cp`)
- Scales numerical features with `StandardScaler`
- Splits data into train/test (80/20 stratified)

---

### Model Layer

**Models trained:** Logistic Regression, Random Forest, SVM, K-Nearest Neighbors, XGBoost (Gradient Boosting)

#### [NEW] [train.py](file:///c:/Users/RABUL/Desktop/mll/src/train.py)
- Trains all 5 classifiers on preprocessed data
- Uses `GridSearchCV` for hyperparameter tuning on best model
- Saves each model as a `.pkl` file

#### [NEW] [evaluate.py](file:///c:/Users/RABUL/Desktop/mll/src/evaluate.py)
- Prints classification report (precision, recall, F1 per class)
- Plots confusion matrix heatmap for each model
- Plots multi-class ROC curves (One-vs-Rest)

#### [NEW] [model_comparison.py](file:///c:/Users/RABUL/Desktop/mll/src/model_comparison.py)
- Bar chart comparing all models by accuracy, macro-F1, training time

